com.astamuse.asta4d.render

Class Renderer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.astamuse.asta4d.render.Renderer
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DebugRenderer, GoThroughRenderer

    public class Renderer
extends Object
    A renderer is for describing rendering actions.

    Developers usually do not need to create a Renderer by constructors directly, alternatively a renderer can be created by calling the static create methods or the add methods.

    Author:
    e-ryu

      • Renderer

        public Renderer(String selector,
        List<Transformer<?>> transformerList)
        Create a Renderer by given css selector and List of Transformer. By given a list, the target element will be duplicated to the same count of Transformer list size.
        Parameters:
        selector - a selector that describes the rendering target element
        transformerList - the action list that describes how to render the target element

      • create

        public static final Renderer create(String selector,
              String value)
        Create a renderer for text by given parameter.

        All child nodes of the target element specified by selector will be emptied and the given String value will be rendered as a single text node of the target element.

        Parameters:
        selector - a css selector
        value - a String value that will be rendered
        Returns:
        the created renderer

      • create

        public static final Renderer create(String selector,
              Object value)
        Create a renderer for given parameter.

        A special typed renderer will be created by the type of the given value. If there is no coordinate renderer for the type of given value, the value#toString() will be used to retrieve a text for rendering.

        Parameters:
        selector - a css selector
        value - a Object that will be rendered.
        Returns:
        the created renderer

      • create

        public static final Renderer create(String selector,
              Renderable renderable)
        Create a renderer for delayed rendering callback

        The target element specified by the given selector will be renderer by the returned value of Renderable.render() which will not be invoked until the target element is actually requiring the rendering action.

        Parameters:
        selector - a css selector
        Renderable - a callback instance of Renderable
        Returns:
        the created renderer

      • create

        public static final Renderer create(String selector,
              Iterable<?> list)
        Create a renderer for list rendering by given parameter.

        The target Element specified by the given selector will be duplicated times as the count of the given list and the contents of the list will be applied to the target Element too.

        Parameters:
        selector - a css selector
        list - a list that can contain all the types supported by the non-list add methods of Renderer
        Returns:
        the created renderer
